# North Star: Reigh Extension Composition Spine

## What we are building

A unified composition spine for Reigh extensions. Clips, shaders, effects, transitions, live data, agent-produced materials, and output formats all participate through a host-projected `CompositionGraph` of contribution refs, typed target paths, graph edges, route requirements, and artifact manifests.

## Why it matters

Without this spine, every new extension family invents its own identity, validation, and mutation path. The spine makes extension contributions first-class, auditable, and composable while keeping the host in control of projection, validation, and execution.

## Immutable constraints

- Extensions and processes never mutate raw timeline internals directly.
- The graph is the authority for graph-authoritative fact families; legacy fields are compatibility inputs only.
- V1 target paths are limited to clip/effect/transition params and shader uniforms.
- Live or nondeterministic inputs must bake or promote to durable materials/artifacts/captures before authoritative export.
- Trusted process runtime and output-format sidecars are real, but they stay namespaced outside the V1 composition SDK.
- No sandbox, marketplace, headless renderer, WebGPU, arbitrary material graphs, shader stacks, FBO chains, or generic texture routing in this epic.

## Success in one sentence

Users can compose, preview, bake, repair, and export video projects using contributions from multiple extensions, and extension authors can declare portable SDK contracts without leaking into host internals.
